text: Presidential elections were held in East Timor on 19 March 2022. Incumbent Francisco Guterres is running for a second term. None of the presidential nominees gotten at least 50% of the votes, so a runoff election was held on 19 April 2022, between the top two candidates, Jos√© Ramos-Horta and Guterres. Ramos-Horta won the runoff with 62% of the total votes cast. ==References== Category:2022 elections in Asia Category:Presidential elections Category:History of East Timor
title: 2022 East Timorese presidential election
